    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - OUTPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="7">
        <title>OUTPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>When removing the rear bearing cover, the rear bearing cone drops from the housing bore.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable tool to drive the output shaft forward and through the rear bearing assembly
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017b2">Figure 112</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017b2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017b2" filename="../figg13/G13017b2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 112. Output Shaft Through Rear Bearing Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear bearing retaining bolts, cover, and gasket from the auxiliary housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017b3">Figure 113</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017b3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017b3" filename="../figg13/G13017b3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 113. Remove Rear Bearing Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the gasket mounting surface of gasket material.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the rear bearing cover oil seal; replace if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017b4">Figure 114</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017b4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017b4" filename="../figg13/G13017b4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 114. Inspect Cover Oil Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing cup and spacer from the auxiliary housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017b5">Figure 115</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017b5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017b5" filename="../figg13/G13017b5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 115. Remove Bearing Cup &#38; Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the remaining bearing cup from the auxiliary housing front (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017b6">Figure 116</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017b6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017b6" filename="../figg13/G13017b6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 116. Remove Remaining Bearing Cup</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing inner spacer from the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017b7">Figure 117</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017b7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017b7" filename="../figg13/G13017b7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 117. Remove Bearing Inner Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the output shaft assembly gear front face as a base and press the output shaft through
                the bearing and gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017b8">Figure 118</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017b8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017b8" filename="../figg13/G13017b8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 118. Output Shaft Through Bearing &#38; Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
